  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_0",
    "text": "Figure 11-4. High-side Switching with an NPN BJT Driving a PNP BJT",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.14312977282043335,
      0.23536706332223556,
      0.7175572582864368,
      0.2529761903063625
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 8
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_7",
    "text": "Low-side switching (Recipe 11.1) is the most common and simplest arrangement, and unless you have a good reason such as the need for one end of the load to be connected to ground, you should use low-side switching.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.14122137182965058,
      0.2732558146517318,
      0.8606870267607253,
      0.3299418602085543
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 9
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_8",
    "text": "See Also",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.14096346855348937,
      0.3452499308352415,
      0.23117393613046996,
      0.36695937108170223
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 10
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_9",
    "text": "For a discussion of NPN and PNP bipolar transistors, see Recipe 5.1.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.14122137182806696,
      0.3793604655139242,
      0.7156488572940704,
      0.39682539656296834
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 11
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_10",
    "text": "GPIO ports and their output logic are described in Recipe 10.7.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.14122137760041995,
      0.4069767444119061,
      0.6717557244988166,
      0.42587209232501233
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 12
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_11",
    "text": "You will find an example of switching with a transistor using an Arduino in Recipe 11.6 and for a Raspberry Pi in Recipe 11.7.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.14122135716362036,
      0.4360119046660272,
      0.8587786284852348,
      0.4724702379192185
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 13
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_12",
    "text": "For switching using a MOSFET, see Recipe 11.3.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.14122137642327962,
      0.48401162844997087,
      0.5458015324316823,
      0.5014880953630427
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 14
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_13",
    "text": "11.3 Switch Much More Power",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.1431297774693976,
      0.5203373011949725,
      0.5190839683593919,
      0.546626983734655
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 15
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_14",
    "text": "Problem",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.14312976963591054,
      0.5639534885545586,
      0.23282442855111238,
      0.5843023250597825
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 16
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_15",
    "text": "You want to allow a GPIO pin to control more power than it otherwise could, but a BJT isn't enough.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.14116426579796448,
      0.5973376699014742,
      0.8588223087056792,
      0.63517441799625
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 17
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_16",
    "text": "Solution",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.1411641776568288,
      0.6539110416139859,
      0.23097322781946206,
      0.673123841972955
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 18
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_17",
    "text": "You can use a MOSFET as an electronic switch. Use the transistor in a commonsource arrangement. Figure 11-5 shows the schematic for this circuit. Along with Recipe 11.1, you will find yourself using this circuit a lot.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.1412213657227804,
      0.6860119046742952,
      0.8606870322187405,
      0.7413194442464224
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 19
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_18",
    "text": "This type of switching is called \"low-side\" switching because the transistor acts as a switch between the low voltage of GND and the load.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.14122137151476513,
      0.7514534887614702,
      0.8587786428363797,
      0.7892441856488664
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 20
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193_19",
    "text": "If the GPIO pin is high (3.3V or 5V) and exceeds the gate-threshold voltage of the MOSFET, the MOSFET will turn on, allowing current to flow from +V through the load to GND.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.13907804095542872,
      0.7993551583714525,
      0.8588373390021741,
      0.8532947455584039
    ],
    "page": "book_en_搬书匠-3246-Electronics Cookbook-2017-英文版_page_193",
    "order": 21
  }
]